preheat oven to 350 degrees F.(175 degrees C).
Cream together the butter, white suger, and brown suger until smooth.
Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Add to batter along with salt.
Stir in flour, choclate chips, and nuts.
Drop by large spoonfulls onto ungreased pans.
Bake for about 10 mins in the preheated oven, or until edges are nicely brown.
